"```sql\nSELECT \n    CAST((balance_end - balance_start) AS REAL) * 100 / balance_start AS increase_rate\nFROM (\n    SELECT \n        (SELECT SUM(trans.balance) \n         FROM trans \n         JOIN disp ON trans.account_id = disp.account_id \n         WHERE disp.client_id = (\n             SELECT disp.client_id \n             FROM loan \n             JOIN disp ON loan.account_id = disp.account_id \n             WHERE loan.date = '1993-07-05' \n             ORDER BY loan.date ASC \n             LIMIT 1\n         ) AND trans.date = '1998-12-27') AS balance_end,\n        (SELECT SUM(trans.balance) \n         FROM trans \n         JOIN disp ON trans.account_id = disp.account_id \n         WHERE disp.client_id = (\n             SELECT disp.client_id \n             FROM loan \n             JOIN disp ON loan.account_id = disp.account_id \n             WHERE loan.date = '1993-07-05' \n             ORDER BY loan.date ASC \n             LIMIT 1\n         ) AND trans.date = '1993-03-22') AS balance_start\n) AS balances\n```\nThis SQL query calculates the increase rate of the account balance for the client whose loan was first approved on 1993-07-05. It does this by finding the sum of balances on two specific dates and then computing the percentage increase."